                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A work containing popular tales relating to the times of the
                            ʿAbbasid Caliphs and the Barmacid family. It was composed by Muhammad
                            Diyāb al-Itlidi around 1100 AH (1688 CE). Present manuscript was copied
                            in 1153 AH (1740 CE).</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_13809-item1">
                            <author key="person_39246492"><persName>Itlīdī, Muḥammad Diyāb, active
                                    17th century</persName> (<persName xml:lang="ar">الاتليدي، محمد
                                    دياب </persName>) </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_955" change="#ids-cleanup"
                                >Iʻlān al-nās bi-mā waqaʻa li-al-Barāmikah min Banī
                                al-ʻAbbās</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_955">إعلام الناس بما وقع للبرامكة مع بني
                                العباس</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="supplied">Tales relating to the times of the
                                'Abbasid Caliphs and the Barmacid family</title>

                            <note>
                                <p>A work containing popular tales relating to the times of the
                                    'Abbasid Caliphs and the Barmacid family.</p><p>Title on folio
                                    1a (and on folio 2a) was given by the author himself and defines
                                    the period to which most of the tales are assigned. In other
                                    respects the title is too narrow.</p>
                                <p>The arrangement is by Caliphs, beginning with ʿUmar b. Khaṭṭāb on
                                    folio 2a and ending with Ibrāhim Muʿtaṣim on folio 161a.</p>
                                <p>Begins (as in Paris 2108): <quote xml:lang="ar">الحمد لله الذي
                                        انول الكتاب ... وبعد فيقول</quote>; ends (fol. 165a): <quote
                                        xml:lang="ar">وقابله حساب نفسه بفعله والله اعلم بفيبه
                                        واحكم</quote>.</p>
                                <p>Colophon on <locus from="165a">folio 165a</locus> gives the date
                                    1153 AH.</p></note>
                            <colophon xml:lang="ar">تم ... يوم السب المبارك غرة رجب سنة ١١٥٣ من
                                الهجرة الخ</colophon>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ar">الحمد الله الذى انزل الكتاب ... وبعد
                                فيقول</incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="ar">وقابله حساب نفسه بفعله والله اعلم بغيبه
                                واحكم</explicit>

                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>

                        </msItem>
